m. The\nrelative wavefunctions in the lives' internal memories govern which lives of\ndifferent systems can meet during future local interactions, and thereby\nenforce entanglement correlations - including Bell inequality violations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 19 Jul 2017 23:37:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 19 Nov 2017 01:24:41 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 27 Oct 2018 03:39:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-11-14"}
