wing to the smaller symmetry\nenergy. As a result, the inner core has smaller masses for the new EOS. It is\nmore compact, on the other hand, due to the softness of the new EOS and bounces\nat higher densities. The ensuing outward propagations of the shock wave in the\nouter core are very similar in the two simulations, which may be an artifact,\nthough, caused by the use of the same tabulated electron capture rates for\nheavy nuclei ignoring differences in the nuclear composition between the two\nEOS's in these computations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 20 Jul 2017 08:18:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-08-01"}
