en comparing Arnett-model results to those obtained from hydrodynamical\ncalculations. We also find that adopting He I and O I line velocities to infer\nthe expansion velocity in He-rich and He-poor SNe, respectively, provides\nejecta masses relatively similar to those obtained by using the Fe II line\nvelocities. The inferred ejecta masses are compatible with intermediate mass\n($M_{ZAMS} \\leq 20$ $M_{\\odot}$) progenitor stars in binary systems for the\nmajority of SE SNe. Furthermore, the majority of our SNe is affected by\nsignificant mixing of $^{56}$Ni, particularly in the case of SNe Ic.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 20 Jul 2017 15:45:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-02-07"}
